<font color="#FF0000">LANGUAGE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan 31 14:57:02 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To all the Guys:<br>
     Thanks for your efforts to curb language here.  I understand Vietnam brings much emotion, but to have the lessons and experiences of the Vietnam generation open to a new generation, we as responsible adults can watch the language we use to describe it.  No, I'm not talking of any kind of censorship, but try to describe experiences without colorful adjectives.  I admit I can curse with the best of them and picked up quite a interesting lot from fellows I served with.  As a teacher, I've learned to handle crisis (you wouldn't believe what happens in school) without using curses.  I had to!!  My job is on the line. Just remember that for the students there are ways to describe feelings without bad language.  Yes, childen hear worse on TV, radio real life etc., but why compound it while educating.  Thanks for listening to my bit fellas.
<p><code>--   (Joe) </code><p>


